And that is coming from this inside the script:
def execute_with_fpga(model_name):
    target='DPUCADX8G'
    vitis_ai_provider_options = {'target': target, 'export_runtime_module': 'vitis_ai_dpu.rtmod'}
    session = onnxruntime.InferenceSession(model_name, None, ["VitisAIExecutionProvider"], [vitis_ai_provider_options])

First thing I see is the target you're passing in is an Alveo DPU, (DPUCADX8G).  The Zync DPUs should typically be DPUCZDX8G.  Change that target on all your scripts.  Since we compile first on x86, you should make sure the first run on x86 also has DPUCZDX8G.
